The paper deals with the stochastic geometry-based characterization of the time-varying performance of a drone cellular network, which involves the analysis of interference, coverage probability, and data rate. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses displacement theorem from stochastic geometry, which is a mathematical tool used in the Mathematics of Operations Research (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper compares its model with more sophisticated mobility models, which involves game theory and optimization, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
